le=Disetujui Menkes, Pekanbaru Siap Terapkan PSBB |url=https://www.beritasatu.com/nasional/619923/disetujui-menkes-pekanbaru-siap-terapkan-psbb |accessdate=15 April 2020 |work=Berita Satu |date=13 April 2020 |language=id}}</ref> The measures are planned to come into effect on 17 April, and will include restrictions on gatherings (requiring permits and limited to five people), a partial [[curfew]] between 8 PM and 5 AM, and capacity restrictions in public transport.<ref>{{cite news |title=PSBB di Pekanbaru, Ini Aturan Baru soal Jam Malam hingga Transportasi |url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/04/14/14303991/psbb-di-pekanbaru-ini-aturan-baru-soal-jam-malam-hingga-transportasi |accessdate=15 April 2020 |work=KOMPAS.com |date=14 April 2020 |language=id}}</ref>\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{COVID-19}}\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Containment efforts related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Country subdivisions lockdowns]] <!-- Because it's a lot of subdivisions locked down separately, not a national decision -->\n[[Category:History of Indonesia]]\n", "name_user": "Juxlos", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Indonesia_large-scale_social_restrictions"}
{"title_page": "Wisconsin Highway 81", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox road\n|state=WI\n|type=WI\n|route=81\n|length_mi=123.81\n|length_ref=\n<ref name=\"WH1\">{{cite web |last = Bessert |first = Chris |title = Wisconsin Highways: Highways 80-89 (Highway 81) |work = Wisconsin Highways |url = http://www.wisconsinhighways.org/listings/WiscHwys80-89.html#STH-081 |accessdate = March 20, 2007 }}{{self-published source|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n|direction_a=West\n|direction_b=East\n|terminus_a={{Jct|state=WI|WI|133}} in [[Cassville, Wisconsin|Cassville]]\n|junction={{Jct|state=WI|US|61|WI|35}} in [[Lancaster, Wisconsin|Lancaster]]<br>{{Jct|state=WI|US|151}} in [[Platteville, Wisconsin|Platteville]]<br>{{Jct|state=WI|US|51}} in [[Beloit, Wisconsin|Beloit]]\n|terminus_b={{Jct|state=WI|I|39|I|43|I|90}} in Beloit\n|counties=[[Grant County, Wisconsin|Grant]], [[Lafayette County, Wisconsin|Lafayette]], [[Green County, Wisconsin|Green]], [[Rock County, Wisconsin|Rock]]\n|previous_type=WI\n|previous_route=80\n|next_type=WI\n|next_route=82\n}}\n'''State Trunk Highway 81''' (often called '''Highway 81''', '''STH-81''' or '''WIS&nbsp;81''') is a [[state highway (US)|state highway]] in the U.S. state of [[Wisconsin]]. It runs east\u2013west in southwest and south central Wisconsin from [[Beloit, Wisconsin|Beloit]] to [[Cassville, Wisconsin|Cassville]]. Between [[Brodhead, Wisconsin|Brodhead]] and [[Monroe, Wisconsin|Monroe]] it [[concurrency (road)|run concurrently]] with [[Wisconsin Highway 11|WIS&nbsp;11]] for {{convert|13|mi}}. The route was originally designated as a state highway in the early 1920s, but there were three different designations along the route. It was not signed as WIS&nbsp;81 along the entire route until 1934.\n[[File:WIS 81 Sign.JPG|thumb|right|Junction at Brodhead with WIS&nbsp;11 and CTH-GG]]\n\n==Route description==\nThe highway begins at an intersection with [[Wisconsin Highway 133|WIS&nbsp;133]] in [[Cassville, Wisconsin|Cassville]], a village along the [[Mississippi River]] bordering [[Iowa]], and runs northeastward from it. It intersects County Trunk Highway U (CTH-U) in [[Beetown (community), Wisconsin|Beetown]] and then [[concurrency (road)|running concurrently]] with [[Wisconsin Highway 33|WIS&nbsp;33]] along the [[Grant River]] west of [[Five Points, Grant County, Wisconsin|Five Points]]. From there, it continues running northeast, intersecting with CTH-N before reaching [[Lancaster, Wisconsin|Lancaster]], where it starts running concurrently with [[U.S. Route 61 in Wisconsin|US Highway&nbsp;61]] (US&nbsp;61). It then runs southeastward, meeting [[Wisconsin Highway 129|WIS&nbsp;129]], an eastern bypass of Lancaster, before exiting its concurrencies with US&nbsp;61 and WIS&nbsp;33. From there. it continues running southeast, passing the [[Ellenboro, Wisconsin|community of Ellenboro]] and running concurrently with CTH-D before entering [[Platteville, Wisconsin|Platteville]] along Lancaster Street. The highway then runs along a few of the streets in Platteville and ends its concurrency with CTH-D before starting another concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 80|WIS&nbsp;80]].<ref name=gmaps/>\n\nThe highway runs southeasterly along the WIS&nbsp;80 concurrency, intersecting with [[U.S. Route 151 Business (Platteville, Wisconsin)|Business US&nbsp;151]] (Bus. US&nbsp;151) before passing through an interchange with [[U.S. Route 151|US 151]]. It then curves to the south, passing by [[Platteville Municipal Airport]] before exiting its concurrency with WIS&nbsp;80 and running east from it. The highway runs directly eastward, passing by [[Elk Grove (community), Wisconsin|Elk Grove]] and intersecting with [[Wisconsin Highway 126|WIS&nbsp;126]] and numerous county trunk highways before running along a short concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 23|WIS&nbsp;23]] in [[Darlington, Wisconsin|Darlington]]. From there, it runs along the [[Pecatonica River]] before it runs south of the highway, and the highway runs east, passing through the [[Lamont (community), Wisconsin|community of Lamont]] before running along a short concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 78|WIS&nbsp;78]] in [[Argyle, Wisconsin|Argyle]].<ref name=gmaps/>\n\nEast of Argyle, the highway runs southeasterly towards [[Monroe, Wisconsin|Monroe]] before running concurrently with [[Wisconsin Highway 11|WIS&nbsp;11]] along a bypass alignment just north of Monroe. The concurrency runs east, passing by [[Juda, Wisconsin|Juda]] before the highway leaves the concurrency and runs southeast from it. The highway curves east in [[Newark, Wisconsin|Newark]] before entering [[Beloit, Wisconsin|Beloit]] along Liberty Avenue. West of the [[Rock River (Mississippi River tributary)|Rock River]], the highway follows a short concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 213|WIS&nbsp;213]]. After crossing the Rock River, the highway intersects [[U.S. Route 51 in Wisconsin|US&nbsp;51]] before running northeast from it and terminating at an interchange with [[Interstate&nbsp;39]]/[[Interstate 90 in Wisconsin|Interstate&nbsp;90]] (I-39/I-90) and continuing as [[Interstate 43|I-43]].<ref name=gmaps/>\n\n==History==\nThe route first appeared as a state trunk highway in the early 1920s, but was split into three differently designated segments: from Cassville to the beginning of the WIS&nbsp;35 (then WIS 65) concurrency, it was WIS&nbsp;105; from the beginning of said concurrency to Monroe, it was part of WIS&nbsp;65; and from the end of the WIS&nbsp;11 (then WIS&nbsp;20), it was part of [[Wisconsin Highway 61|WIS&nbsp;61]].<ref name=\"1921map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Conservation Commission |date = c. 1921 |title = Map of the State Highway System of Wisconsin, Showing, Within Red Circle, Location of Northern Lakes Park |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/singleitem/collection/maps/id/946/rec/36 |scale = Scale not given |location = n.p. |publisher = Wisconsin State Conservation Commission |oclc = 708376740 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> In 1924, the entire route was signed as a western extension of WIS&nbsp;61.<ref name=\"1924map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin Motorists Association |year = 1924 |title = Our Map of Wisconsin |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/maps/id/14655/rec/63 |scale = Scale not given |location = Milwaukee |publisher = Wisconsin Motorists Association |oclc = 664274042 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> In 1927, the highway, along with the rest of WIS&nbsp;61, had been renumbered to WIS&nbsp;14.<ref name=\"1927map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |year = 1927 |title = Official Highway Map of Wisconsin: 'The Playground of the Middle West' |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/singleitem/collection/maps/id/14114/rec/42 |scale = 1:950,400  |location = Madison  |publisher = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |oclc = 671337231 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> In 1934, when [[U.S. Route 14 in Wisconsin|US&nbsp;14]] was designated within the state, the entire route was renumbered to WIS&nbsp;81.<ref name=\"1934map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |year = 1934 |title = Official Highway Map of Wisconsin 1934 |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/maps/id/14147/rec/47 |scale = 1:823,680 |location = Madison |publisher = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |oclc = 227048467 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> Between 1948 and 1956, the entire route within [[Grant County, Wisconsin|Grant County]] was paved. The sections which were not paved in 1956 were the entire route in [[Lafayette County, Wisconsin|Lafayette County]], between the WIS&nbsp;11 concurrency and Newark, and a short section along the WIS&nbsp;11 concurrency near Juda.<ref name=\"1948map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |year = 1948 |title = Preliminary Traffic Map, Showing Annual 24 Hour Average Traffic, State of Wisconsin |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/singleitem/collection/maps/id/14173/rec/69 |scale = c. 1:1,198,000 |location = Madison |publisher = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |oclc = 770711221 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"1956map\">{{cite web |author1 = Wisconsin Highway Commission |year = 1956 |title = Wisconsin State Atlas 1956 Highway Maps |url = http://www.historicmapworks.com/Atlas/US/9643/Wisconsin+State+Atlas+1956+Highway+Maps/ |location = Madison |publisher = Wisconsin Highway Commission |via = Historic Map Works |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Major junctions==\n{{Jcttop|length_ref=<ref name=gmaps>{{google maps |url = https://www.google.com/maps/dir/42.7143934,-90.9907411/42.8268215,-90.6886779/42.7139137,-90.45725/42.6678303,-90.3293715/42.7012417,-89.8744528/42.6169332,-89.6367084/42.6080997,-89.619705/42.5108113,-89.0556888/42.508308,-89.0318151/42.5265815,-88.9775177/@42.6767723,-90.5446038,9z/am=t/data=!3m1!4b1!4m17!4m16!1m5!3m4!1m2!1d-90.7123217!2d42.8469975!3s0x87fcdd9dd5f2b18d:0x11a3263642db3e32!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!3e0 |title = Length and Route of WIS&nbsp;81 |access-date = April 10, 2020 }}</ref>}}\n{{WIint\n|county=Grant\n|cspan=8\n|location=Cassville\n|mile=0.0\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|133}}\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|mile=11.6\n|location=Beetown\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|35|dir1=north}}\n|notes=Western end of WIS&nbsp;35 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|location=Lancaster\n|mile=18.8\n|type=concur\n|road={{jct|state=WI|US|61|dir1=north}}\n|notes=Northern end of US&nbsp;61 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|location=South Lancaster\n|lspan=2\n|mile=20.8\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|129|dir1=north}}\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|mile=21.6\n|road={{jct|state=WI|US|61|WIS|35|dir1=south|dir2=south}}\n|notes=Southern end of US&nbsp;61/WIS&nbsp;35 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|location=Platteville\n|mile=34.8\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|80|dir1=north}}\n|notes=Northern end of WIS&nbsp;80 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|location1=Platteville\n|location2=Platteville (town)\n|ctdab2=Grant\n|mile=36.5\n|road={{jct|state=WI|US|151}}\n|notes=Interchange\n}}\n{{WIint\n|location=Smelser\n|mile=40.2\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|80|dir1=South}}\n|notes=Southern end of WIS&nbsp;80 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|county=Lafayette\n|cspan=5\n|location=Elk Grove\n|mile=45.6\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|126|dir1=north}}\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|location1=Darlington\n|location2=Darlington (town)\n|mile=55.8\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|23|dir1=south}}\n|notes=Southern end of WIS&nbsp;23 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|location=Darlington\n|mile=56.9\n|type=concur\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|23|dir1=north}}\n|notes=Northern end of WIS&nbsp;23 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|location=Argyle\n|lspan=2\n|mile=71.7\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|78|dir1=south}}\n|notes=Western end of WIS&nbsp;78 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|mile=72.1\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|78|dir1=north}}\n|notes=Eastern end of WIS&nbsp;78 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|county=Green\n|cspan=4\n|town=Monroe\n|ctdab=Green\n|lspan=2\n|mile=85.7\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|11|WI|69|dir1=west|dir2=south}}\n|notes=Western end of WIS&nbsp;11/WIS&nbsp;69 concurrency; interchange\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|mile=86.6\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|69|dir1=north}}\n|notes=Eastern end of WIS&nbsp;69 concurrency; interchange\n}}\n{{WIint\n|mile=87.7\n|location1=Monroe (town)\n|location2=Monroe\n|ctdab1=Green\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WIS|59|dir1=east}}\n|notes=Interchange\n}}\n{{WIint\n|mile=99.5\n|location=Spring Grove\n|type=concur\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WIS|11|CTH|GG|dir1=east|dir2=north}}\n|notes=Eastern end of WIS&nbsp;11 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|type=concur\n|county=Rock\n|cspan=4\n|location=Beloit\n|lspan=4\n|mile=118.5\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|213|dir1=north}}\n|notes=Western end of WIS&nbsp;213 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|mile=119.7\n|type=concur\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|213|dir1=south}}\n|notes=Eastern end of WIS&nbsp;213 concurrency\n}}\n{{WIint\n|mile=120.0\n|road={{jct|state=WI|US|51}}\n}}\n{{WIint\n|mile=123.1\n|road={{jct|state=WI|I|39|I|90|city1=Madison|location2=[[Rockford, Illinois|Rockford]]}}<br/>{{jct|state=WI|I|43|dir1=east|city1=Milwaukee}}\n|notes=Interchange\n}}\n{{jctbtm|keys=concur}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:State highways in Wisconsin|081]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Grant County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Lafayette County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Green County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Rock County, Wisconsin]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox road\n|state=WI\n|type=WI\n|route=81\n|length_mi=123.81\n|length_ref=\n<ref name=\"WH1\">{{cite web |last = Bessert |first = Chris |title = Wisconsin Highways: Highways 80-89 (Highway 81) |work = Wisconsin Highways |url = http://www.wisconsinhighways.org/listings/WiscHwys80-89.html#STH-081 |accessdate = March 20, 2007 }}{{self-published source|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n|direction_a=West\n|direction_b=East\n|terminus_a={{Jct|state=WI|WI|133}} in [[Cassville, Wisconsin|Cassville]]\n|junction={{Jct|state=WI|US|61|WI|35}} in [[Lancaster, Wisconsin|Lancaster]]<br>{{Jct|state=WI|US|151}} in [[Platteville, Wisconsin|Platteville]]<br>{{Jct|state=WI|US|51}} in [[Beloit, Wisconsin|Beloit]]\n|terminus_b={{Jct|state=WI|I|39|I|43|I|90}} in Beloit\n|counties=[[Grant County, Wisconsin|Grant]], [[Lafayette County, Wisconsin|Lafayette]], [[Green County, Wisconsin|Green]], [[Rock County, Wisconsin|Rock]]\n|previous_type=WI\n|previous_route=80\n|next_type=WI\n|next_route=82\n}}\n'''State Trunk Highway 81''' (often called '''Highway 81''', '''STH-81''' or '''WIS&nbsp;81''') is a [[state highway (US)|state highway]] in the U.S. state of [[Wisconsin]]. It runs east\u2013west in southwest and south central Wisconsin from [[Beloit, Wisconsin|Beloit]] to [[Cassville, Wisconsin|Cassville]]. Between [[Brodhead, Wisconsin|Brodhead]] and [[Monroe, Wisconsin|Monroe]] it [[concurrency (road)|run concurrently]] with [[Wisconsin Highway 11|WIS&nbsp;11]] for {{convert|13|mi}}. The route was originally designated as a state highway in the early 1920s, but there were three different designations along the route. It was not signed as WIS&nbsp;81 along the entire route until 1934.\n[[File:WIS 81 Sign.JPG|thumb|right|Junction at Brodhead with WIS&nbsp;11 and CTH-GG]]\n\n==Route description==\nThe highway begins at an intersection with [[Wisconsin Highway 133|WIS&nbsp;133]] in [[Cassville, Wisconsin|Cassville]], a village along the [[Mississippi River]] bordering [[Iowa]], and runs northeastward from it. It intersects County Trunk Highway U (CTH-U) in [[Beetown (community), Wisconsin|Beetown]] and then [[concurrency (road)|running concurrently]] with [[Wisconsin Highway 33|WIS&nbsp;33]] along the [[Grant River]] west of [[Five Points, Grant County, Wisconsin|Five Points]]. From there, it continues running northeast, intersecting with CTH-N before reaching [[Lancaster, Wisconsin|Lancaster]], where it starts running concurrently with [[U.S. Route 61 in Wisconsin|US Highway&nbsp;61]] (US&nbsp;61). It then runs southeastward, meeting [[Wisconsin Highway 129|WIS&nbsp;129]], an eastern bypass of Lancaster, before exiting its concurrencies with US&nbsp;61 and WIS&nbsp;33. From there. it continues running southeast, passing the [[Ellenboro, Wisconsin|community of Ellenboro]] and running concurrently with CTH-D before entering [[Platteville, Wisconsin|Platteville]] along Lancaster Street. The highway then runs along a few of the streets in Platteville and ends its concurrency with CTH-D before starting another concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 80|WIS&nbsp;80]].<ref name=gmaps/>\n\nThe highway runs southeasterly along the WIS&nbsp;80 concurrency, intersecting with [[U.S. Route 151 Business (Platteville, Wisconsin)|Business US&nbsp;151]] (Bus. US&nbsp;151) before passing through an interchange with [[U.S. Route 151|US 151]]. It then curves to the south, passing by [[Platteville Municipal Airport]] before exiting its concurrency with WIS&nbsp;80 and running east from it. The highway runs directly eastward, passing by [[Elk Grove (community), Wisconsin|Elk Grove]] and intersecting with [[Wisconsin Highway 126|WIS&nbsp;126]] and numerous county trunk highways before running along a short concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 23|WIS&nbsp;23]] in [[Darlington, Wisconsin|Darlington]]. From there, it runs along the [[Pecatonica River]] before it runs south of the highway, and the highway runs east, passing through the [[Lamont (community), Wisconsin|community of Lamont]] before running along a short concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 78|WIS&nbsp;78]] in [[Argyle, Wisconsin|Argyle]].<ref name=gmaps/>\n\nEast of Argyle, the highway runs southeasterly towards [[Monroe, Wisconsin|Monroe]] before running concurrently with [[Wisconsin Highway 11|WIS&nbsp;11]] along a bypass alignment just north of Monroe. The concurrency runs east, passing by [[Juda, Wisconsin|Juda]] before the highway leaves the concurrency and runs southeast from it. The highway curves east in [[Newark, Wisconsin|Newark]] before entering [[Beloit, Wisconsin|Beloit]] along Liberty Avenue. West of the [[Rock River (Mississippi River tributary)|Rock River]], the highway follows a short concurrency with [[Wisconsin Highway 213|WIS&nbsp;213]]. After crossing the Rock River, the highway intersects [[U.S. Route 51 in Wisconsin|US&nbsp;51]] before running northeast from it and terminating at an interchange with [[Interstate&nbsp;39]]/[[Interstate 90 in Wisconsin|Interstate&nbsp;90]] (I-39/I-90) and continuing as [[Interstate 43|I-43]].<ref name=gmaps/>\n\n==History==\nThe route first appeared as a state trunk highway in the early 1920s, but was split into three differently designated segments: from Cassville to the beginning of the WIS&nbsp;35 (then WIS 65) concurrency, it was WIS&nbsp;105; from the beginning of said concurrency to Monroe, it was part of WIS&nbsp;65; and from the end of the WIS&nbsp;11 (then WIS&nbsp;20), it was part of [[Wisconsin Highway 61|WIS&nbsp;61]].<ref name=\"1921map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Conservation Commission |date = c. 1921 |title = Map of the State Highway System of Wisconsin, Showing, Within Red Circle, Location of Northern Lakes Park |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/singleitem/collection/maps/id/946/rec/36 |scale = Scale not given |location = n.p. |publisher = Wisconsin State Conservation Commission |oclc = 708376740 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> In 1924, the entire route was signed as a western extension of WIS&nbsp;61.<ref name=\"1924map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin Motorists Association |year = 1924 |title = Our Map of Wisconsin |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/maps/id/14655/rec/63 |scale = Scale not given |location = Milwaukee |publisher = Wisconsin Motorists Association |oclc = 664274042 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> In 1927, the highway, along with the rest of WIS&nbsp;61, had been renumbered to WIS&nbsp;14.<ref name=\"1927map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |year = 1927 |title = Official Highway Map of Wisconsin: 'The Playground of the Middle West' |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/singleitem/collection/maps/id/14114/rec/42 |scale = 1:950,400  |location = Madison  |publisher = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |oclc = 671337231 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> In 1934, when [[U.S. Route 14 in Wisconsin|US&nbsp;14]] was designated within the state, the entire route was renumbered to WIS&nbsp;81.<ref name=\"1934map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |year = 1934 |title = Official Highway Map of Wisconsin 1934 |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/maps/id/14147/rec/47 |scale = 1:823,680 |location = Madison |publisher = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |oclc = 227048467 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref> Between 1948 and 1956, the entire route within [[Grant County, Wisconsin|Grant County]] was paved. The sections which were not paved in 1956 were the entire route in [[Lafayette County, Wisconsin|Lafayette County]], between the WIS&nbsp;11 concurrency and Newark, and a short section along the WIS&nbsp;11 concurrency near Juda.<ref name=\"1948map\">{{cite map |author1 = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |year = 1948 |title = Preliminary Traffic Map, Showing Annual 24 Hour Average Traffic, State of Wisconsin |url = http://content.wisconsinhistory.org/cdm/singleitem/collection/maps/id/14173/rec/69 |scale = c. 1:1,198,000 |location = Madison |publisher = Wisconsin State Highway Commission |oclc = 770711221 |via = Wisconsin Historical Society |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"1956map\">{{cite web |author1 = Wisconsin Highway Commission |year = 1956 |title = Wisconsin State Atlas 1956 Highway Maps |url = http://www.historicmapworks.com/Atlas/US/9643/Wisconsin+State+Atlas+1956+Highway+Maps/ |location = Madison |publisher = Wisconsin Highway Commission |via = Historic Map Works |access-date = April 11, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Major junctions==\n{{Jcttop|length_ref=<ref name=gmaps>{{google maps |url = https://www.google.com/maps/dir/42.7143934,-90.9907411/42.8268215,-90.6886779/42.7139137,-90.45725/42.6678303,-90.3293715/42.7012417,-89.8744528/42.6169332,-89.6367084/42.6080997,-89.619705/42.5108113,-89.0556888/42.508308,-89.0318151/42.5265815,-88.9775177/@42.6767723,-90.5446038,9z/am=t/data=!3m1!4b1!4m17!4m16!1m5!3m4!1m2!1d-90.7123217!2d42.8469975!3s0x87fcdd9dd5f2b18d:0x11a3263642db3e32!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m0!3e0 |